text.paragraph:
For patients with severe renal impairment (CLcr <30 mL/min), a daily dose of VESIcare greater than 5 mg is not recommended [see Warnings and Precautions (5.6); 
                                 Use in Specific Populations
                               (8.6)].

For patients with moderate hepatic impairment (Child-Pugh B), a daily dose of VESIcare greater than 5 mg is not recommended. Use of VESIcare in patients with severe hepatic impairment (Child-Pugh C) is not recommended [see Warnings and Precautions (
                                 5.5
                              ); 
                                 Use in Specific Populations
                               (8.7)].

Solifenacin has no significant effect on the pharmacokinetics of R-warfarin or S-warfarin [see 
                                 Clinical Pharmacology (12.3


                           )].

In the presence of solifenacin there are no significant changes in the plasma concentrations of combined oral contraceptives (ethinyl estradiol/levonorgestrel) [see 
                                 Clinical Pharmacology (12.3


                           )].

Solifenacin had no significant effect on the pharmacokinetics of digoxin (0.125 mg/day) in healthy subjects [see 
                                 Clinical Pharmacology (12.3


                           )].

VESIcare should be used with caution in patients with renal impairment. There is a 2.1-fold increase in AUC and 1.6-fold increase in t1/2 of solifenacin in patients with severe renal impairment. Doses of VESIcare greater than 5 mg are not recommended in patients with severe renal impairment (CLcr < 30 mL/min) [see 
                                 Warnings and Precautions (5.6)

                           ; 

                                 Dosage and Administration (2.2
                              )].
